select count(*) as aggregate from `items` left join `categories` on `categories`.`category_id` = `items`.`item_categoryid` left join `pinned` on `pinned`.`pinnedresource_id` = `items`.`item_id` and `pinned`.`pinnedresource_type` = 'item' and `pinned`.`pinned_userid` = 1 where 1 = 1 and `item_id` = '7'

select * from `items` left join `categories` on `categories`.`category_id` = `items`.`item_categoryid` left join `pinned` on `pinned`.`pinnedresource_id` = `items`.`item_id` and `pinned`.`pinnedresource_type` = 'item' and `pinned`.`pinned_userid` = 1 where 1 = 1 and `item_id` = '7' order by CASE WHEN pinned.pinned_id IS NOT NULL THEN 0 ELSE 1 END, `pinned`.`pinned_id` desc, `item_id` desc limit 35 offset 0
select count(*) as aggregate from `types` where 1 = 1

select *, (SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM items
WHERE id = types.id)
AS count_items from `types` where 1 = 1 order by `id` asc limit 35 offset 0
